      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(config): skip shell env fallback on Windows",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #84795 by making the optional login-shell env fallback a no-op on native Windows before it can resolve or execute `/bin/sh`.\n\nThe existing POSIX behavior is unchanged. `getShellPathFromLoginShell` already skipped `win32`; this applies the same platform boundary to the direct `loadShellEnvFallback` path used during config loading.\n\n## Verification\n\n2026-05-23 update after rebasing onto `origin/main` (`acf265d4d5`), head `8ef82383f5`:\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/shell-env.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (1 file, 21 tests passed)\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 CHANGELOG.md src/infra/shell-env.ts src/infra/shell-env.test.ts`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxlint src/infra/shell-env.ts src/infra/shell-env.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n\nEarlier verification before the rebase:\n\n- `corepack pnpm install`\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 CHANGELOG.md src/infra/shell-env.ts src/infra/shell-env.test.ts`\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxlint src/infra/shell-env.ts src/infra/shell-env.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- Testbox-through-Crabbox, provider `blacksmith-testbox`, id `tbx_01ksam41ew6rr7b0zmwf5hacq7`, Actions run https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/actions/runs/26335373158:\n  `CI=1 NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=4096 OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 OPENCLAW_VITEST_NO_OUTPUT_TIMEOUT_MS=900000 OPENCLAW_TESTBOX=1 OPENCLAW_TESTBOX_REMOTE_RUN=1 corepack pnpm test src/infra/shell-env.test.ts`\n  - Result: 1 file / 21 tests passed.\n- Autoreview: `/mnt/c/src/claws-hapi/.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n  - Result: clean, no accepted/actionable findings.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: With `OPENCLAW_LOAD_SHELL_ENV=1` or config-driven shell env import enabled on native Windows, OpenClaw should not try to execute `/bin/sh` and should not emit `[openclaw] shell env fallback failed: spawnSync /bin/sh ENOENT`.\n\nReal environment tested: WSL Ubuntu-24.04 checkout at `/root/src/openclaw-85739`, Node/Vitest via repo wrapper. Earlier proof also ran on Blacksmith Testbox through Crabbox (`provider=blacksmith-testbox`, id `tbx_01ksam41ew6rr7b0zmwf5hacq7`, GitHub Actions run https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/actions/runs/26335373158).\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/shell-env.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n\nEvidence after fix: The `shell-env` regression test calls `loadShellEnvFallback` with `platform: \"win32\"`, a missing expected key, and an `exec` stub that would throw `spawnSync /bin/sh ENOENT` if the POSIX shell probe ran. The result is `{ ok: true, applied: [] }`, the exec stub is not called, and no warning is logged.\n\nObserved result after fix: The native Windows platform branch returns an empty shell-env probe result before shell resolution, so no `/bin/sh` process is attempted and no fallback warning is emitted. The focused suite passed 21 tests.\n\nWhat was not tested: I did not complete a full native Windows `openclaw status` smoke from this WSL worktree because Windows Node was blocked from importing files from the WSL filesystem with `Access is denied`. The tested behavior is the exact internal fallback branch that caused the warning.\n",
        "branch": "fix-84795-win32-shell-env-fallback",
